The paper discusses a methodology and philosophy of empirical science based on large scale lossless data compression. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category, which deals with the study of information processing, including compression. The paper also discusses the application of this methodology to fields such as computer vision and computational linguistics, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes the empirical nature of this research, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category, which deals with the study of efficient data storage and retrieval.
